19_141>Namaste friends,<BR> <BR>Someone with psychiatric problems may =
expereience what sounds like a Kundalini rise, but it may or may not be one=
.<BR> <BR>It must be conceded though that Kundalini spontaneously risi=
ng through various nadis without one having gone through proper preparation=
 in this life (i.e. fine-tuning of one's attitude and development of detach=
ment) CAN create havoc!<BR> <BR>One may wonder how Kundalini may spont=
aneously rise in a layman with no sadhana, while many serious sadhakas may =
not experience it.<BR> <BR>Firstly, Kundalini rise is NOT an achieveme=
nt. It is just A SMALL STEP in overcoming one's current limited identity.<B=
R> <BR>Let me give an analogy. One wanting to move from one's small di=
lapidated house (this body-mind complex) to a huge palace (realized Self) m=
ay first construct the palace over time and
 move into it when it is COMPLE=
TE. Alternately, if one occasionally goes and stays in the palace still und=
er construction (analogy for out of body experiences due to Kundalini rise)=
, is it an achievement? In fact, it comes with risks. The former approach i=
s safer and one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one can progress towards co=
mplete Self-realization without any out of body experiences. These are not =
my word's, but Maharshi Vasishtha's words to Lord Rama.<BR> <BR>Second=
ly, one does not get something without wanting it and putting sufficient ef=
fort towards it. One may have deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previous=
 life and may have put enough effort. As a result, one may be getting it no=
w. But one may be unprepared (and ironically may not even want it!) when it=
 comes in this life.<BR> <BR>As you do sadhana, try not to fancy too m=
any specific desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires=
 (because of constraints on what
 Nature can give you right now, arising fr=
om YOUR OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want =
LATE, when you no longer want it or want something else. For example, one m=
ay pray for great wealth one's whole life and be born as a rich but very si=
ck man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for =
health. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any k=
nowledge or money. </SPAN><SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_19_136206784661=
9_141>In another case, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One m=
ay be reborn as a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really e=
njoy that experience. Basically, people </SPAN><SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_=
3_7_2_19_1362067846619_141>keep going in circles through various lives, alw=
ays "seeking" something they are "missing".<BR> <BR>Anyway, coming bac=
k to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given by a =
rising Kundalini and one's
 previous karmas constrain one from having it in=
 THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire destined=
 to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).<BR> <BR>*&nb=
sp;       *     &nbs=
p;  *<BR> <BR>Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful,=
 if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.<BR> <BR>=
Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it panic=
ked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it from a certa=
in slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!<BR> <BR>We are l=
ike that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex an=
d scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!<BR> <BR>If our id=
eas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect and=
 if we are this "infinite Self" as shastras say, won't a complete realizati=
on of that at some
 stage involve stepping out of this body-mind complex, w=
ithout being scared?<BR> <BR>*      &nbs=
p; *        *<BR> <BR>Kundalini ris=
e after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better than Kunda=
lini rise forced when some really undesirable conditioning is still left in=
 one's system.<BR> <BR>When one transcends one problematic notion abou=
t who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay buried deeper in c=
onsciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. If one overcomes th=
e notion "I am the body", there may be another notion in one's body-mind co=
mplex that one's awareness clings on to (</SPAN><SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui=
_3_7_2_19_1362067846619_141><SPAN class=3Dyiv1490316537userContent>e.g. a g=
reat doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc</SPAN>). As=
 an extreme example, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great s=
oul who rescues
 the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y =
who will rescue the world now. When one's self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) =
deeply clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show s=
ome signs of progress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.<BR>&=
nbsp;<BR>An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesirable conditioning ma=
y accentuate one's weaknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious p=
sychiatric and spiritual problems.<BR> <BR>*    &n=
bsp;   *        *<BR> <BR=
 id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_19_1362067846619_158>The best approach I recom=
mend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, o=
vercome your weaknesses and improve your detachment over time. Again, I wan=
t to emphasize that detachment is not disgust or distaste for life/things/p=
eople around you. Disgust is the other side of coin of attachment.</SPAN> I=
t is a
 negative attachment.  </DIV>
<DIV style=3D"BACKGROUND-COLOR: t=
ransparent; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; =
COLOR: rgb(0,0,0); FONT-SIZE: 13px" id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_19_13620678=
46619_155>D<SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_19_1362067846619_141>on't worr=
y about whether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are ab=
le to resist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) o=
r not. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you are making progres=
s. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making progress. Wh=
en you completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) will autom=
atically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).</SPAN></DIV>
