p;    *<BR> <BR>One word on surrendering to a personal =
deity. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They s=
imply do business with god. Though people may be offended by my words, this=
 is the plain and bare fact.<BR> <BR>"I want X, </SPAN><SPAN id=3Dyiv1=
490316537yui_3_7_2_19_1362067846619_141><SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_1=
9_1362067846619_141>I will pray to you and </SPAN>please give it to me", "I=
 am scared of Kundalini rise, I will pray to you and please protect me" - a=
ll this is just a business deal. There is something you want and you ask go=
d
 for it. True surrender has no place for agendas, desires, demands or exp=
ectations. True surrender is losing oneself in one's fascination for the qu=
alities of Lord. True surrender is accepting anything Lord throws one's way=
 (whether it is pleasurable or highly painful) as Lord's prasad and accepti=
ng it gratefully. True surrender is thinking of Lord with fascination and p=
leasure, even in the face of (and during) Death.<BR> <BR>If one withou=
t true surrender and with many desires and wrong notions experiences a Kund=
alini rise, one may still be trapped, despite thinking of a personal god. I=
t is not that god does not want to "protect" one as said below. It is not a=
bout protecting or endangering. If you go back to my "chipmunk glued to mou=
se trap" example above, I was trying to protect it, but it was scared. Simi=
larly, one's conditioning makes one *run away* from God's protection! God's=
 protection may seem to a conditioned mind like grave danger that one
 shou=
ld run away from!<BR> <BR></SPAN><SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_19_=
1362067846619_141><SPAN id=3Dyiv1490316537yui_3_7_2_19_1362067846619_141>*&=
nbsp;       *     &n=
bsp;  *<BR> <BR></SPAN>Whether through the path of wisdom or surr=
ender, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporar=
y and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing you=
r best, but be prepared to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and a v=
ery light mental conditioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protec=
t one as one's Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and im=
purities in one's nadis will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and=
 stop Her from meeting True Self.<BR> <BR>The real key is how light yo=
ur conditioning is.<BR> <BR></SPAN>Best regards, Narasimha -------- As=
